The paper discusses a deep learning architecture and algorithm for question answering with knowledge graphs, which is a common topic in natural language processing (NLP) and artificial intelligence (AI) research. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves learning and optimization techniques, which are relevant to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper deals with knowledge graphs, which are a type of database, making cs.DB (Databases) a possible sub-category as well.
